A rose pink corset, designed by Jean-Paul Gaultier  and worn by pop star Madonna during her 1990 concert tour, was sold for 12,100  pounds (18,150 dollars) at Christie's auction house, London, on Thursday.
Also in the sale of pop memorabilia, which fetched a total of 335,885  pounds (503,830 dollars), was an alto saxophone signed by American President  Bill Clinton and members of rock group Fleetwood Mac, which fetched 22,000  (33,000 dollars).
At the other end of the musical scale, love-letters from composer Dmitri  Shostakovich to his mistress Elena Konstantinovskaya, a 20-year-old language  student, were sold for 10,925 pounds (16,388 dollars) at Sotheby's, London.
